meanings.definition: Not feeling or showing satisfaction or contentment; not complacent.
meanings.sent1: She was uncomplacent about her grades, always striving for improvement.
meanings.sent2: The team remained uncomplacent despite their recent success, pushing themselves to do better.
meanings.sent3: The uncomplacent student eagerly sought feedback to enhance her work.
meanings.sent4: His uncomplacent attitude towards challenges made him a valuable team member.
meanings.sent5: The uncomplacent gardener constantly experimented with new techniques to improve his plants' growth.

meanings.definition: Not self-satisfied or smug; not complacent.
meanings.sent1: The uncomplacent artist was always looking for ways to evolve her style.
meanings.sent2: She maintained an uncomplacent approach to her career, always seeking new opportunities.
meanings.sent3: The uncomplacent child eagerly tackled each new puzzle with enthusiasm.
meanings.sent4: His uncomplacent demeanor in the face of success impressed his colleagues.
meanings.sent5: The uncomplacent explorer never settled for the familiar, always venturing into uncharted territories.
